---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Scenes / The Work — Eliyannah Amirah Yisrael"
  description="The working filmography of Eliyannah Amirah Yisrael — feature, webseries, commercial, and music video credits."
  pageSlug="scenes"
  pageNumber={2}
>

<main class="main">
  <section class="page">
    <div class="page-eyebrow">Section 02 · Scenes</div>
    <h1 class="page-title">The <em>Work</em></h1>
    <p class="page-subtitle">
      Every project is a scene. Every scene is the whole argument for what comes next.
    </p>

    <div class="scenes-grid">

      <!-- SCENE 01 -->
      <article class="scene-entry">
        <div class="scene-entry-number">01</div>
        <div class="scene-entry-body">
          <div class="scene-entry-main">
            <div class="scene-slugline">INT. Chicago — 2026 — Day · Feature Film · In Development</div>
            <h2 class="scene-entry-title"><em>The Caterpillar</em> and <em>The Butterfly</em></h2>
            <div class="scene-entry-tagline">
              A South Side mother and daughter. One summer. Becoming, and what it costs.
            </div>
            <div class="scene-entry-synopsis">
              <p>Ronnie and TaLisha do not know each other. They ride the same bus on the south side of Chicago. Over the course of one spring, they trade places in the metaphor — the caterpillar and the butterfly, moving in opposite emotional directions. They speak twice: once at the beginning of the journey, once at the end.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="scene-entry-actions">
              <a href="#" class="primary">Open Film Site →</a>
              <a href="#">Script (Password)</a>
              <a href="#">Lookbook</a>
            </div>
          </div>
          <aside class="scene-entry-meta">
            <div class="scene-meta-row"><span class="key">Scene</span><span class="val">01</span></div>
            <div class="scene-meta-row"><span class="key">Status</span><span class="val"><em>In Development</em></span></div>
            <div class="scene-meta-row"><span class="key">Writer</span><span class="val">E.A. Yisrael</span></div>
            <div class="scene-meta-row"><span class="key">Director</span><span class="val">E.A. Yisrael</span></div>
            <div class="scene-meta-row"><span class="key">Setting</span><span class="val">Chicago, IL</span></div>
            <div class="scene-meta-row"><span class="key">Format</span><span class="val">Feature · Film</span></div>
          </aside>
        </div>
      </article>

      <!-- SCENE 02 -->
      <article class="scene-entry">
        <div class="scene-entry-number">02</div>
        <div class="scene-entry-body">
          <div class="scene-entry-main">
            <div class="scene-slugline">INT. / EXT. Various — 2016–2017 · Webseries · Completed</div>
            <h2 class="scene-entry-title"><em>Hermione Granger</em> and the Quarter Life Crisis</h2>
            <div class="scene-entry-tagline">
              Hermione Granger, Black, Brooklyn, broke, and grown. The quarter-life crisis as a two-season arc.
            </div>
            <div class="scene-entry-synopsis">
              <p>Two seasons of a Black Hermione in her mid-twenties — working, broke, trying to make a life the books never imagined for her and the films refused to. Festival selections, press in PBS, <em>Emmy</em> magazine, <em>The Los Angeles Times</em>, and <em>Elle UK</em>.</p>
              <p>Credited as creator, showrunner, director, and writer. The project that built the audience and proved the voice.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="scene-entry-actions">
              <a href="#" class="primary">Watch Episode 101 →</a>
              <a href="#">Season 2 Premiere</a>
              <a href="/press">Press Coverage</a>
            </div>
          </div>
          <aside class="scene-entry-meta">
            <div class="scene-meta-row"><span class="key">Scene</span><span class="val">02</span></div>
            <div class="scene-meta-row"><span class="key">Status</span><span class="val"><em>Released</em></span></div>
            <div class="scene-meta-row"><span class="key">Seasons</span><span class="val">Two</span></div>
            <div class="scene-meta-row"><span class="key">Role</span><span class="val">Creator · Showrunner · Director · Writer</span></div>
            <div class="scene-meta-row"><span class="key">Press</span><span class="val">PBS · Emmy · LA Times · Elle UK</span></div>
            <div class="scene-meta-row"><span class="key">Format</span><span class="val">Digital Series</span></div>
          </aside>
        </div>
      </article>

      <!-- SCENE 03 -->
      <article class="scene-entry">
        <div class="scene-entry-number">03</div>
        <div class="scene-entry-body">
          <div class="scene-entry-main">
            <div class="scene-slugline">INT. Studio — Day · Short Narrative · Completed</div>
            <h2 class="scene-entry-title"><em>The Life</em> I Carry</h2>
            <div class="scene-entry-tagline">
              <span class="prompt small">One-line tagline. Your voice.</span>
            </div>
            <div class="scene-entry-synopsis">
              <span class="prompt">Two- to three-sentence synopsis. What the short is. Who's in it. What it does.</span>
            </div>
            <div class="scene-entry-actions">
              <a href="#" class="primary">Watch →</a>
            </div>
          </div>
          <aside class="scene-entry-meta">
            <div class="scene-meta-row"><span class="key">Scene</span><span class="val">03</span></div>
            <div class="scene-meta-row"><span class="key">Status</span><span class="val"><em>Released</em></span></div>
            <div class="scene-meta-row"><span class="key">Runtime</span><span class="val">19:49</span></div>
            <div class="scene-meta-row"><span class="key">Role</span><span class="val">Director · Writer</span></div>
            <div class="scene-meta-row"><span class="key">Format</span><span class="val">Short Film</span></div>
          </aside>
        </div>
      </article>

      <!-- SCENE 04 -->
      <article class="scene-entry">
        <div class="scene-entry-number">04</div>
        <div class="scene-entry-body">
          <div class="scene-entry-main">
            <div class="scene-slugline">EXT. Various — Day · Commercial &amp; Music Video · Completed</div>
            <h2 class="scene-entry-title">Commercial <em>&amp;</em> Music Video</h2>
            <div class="scene-entry-tagline">
              Mik Jacobi. bigbellyrelli. Tetris for Coachella. The commissioned work that keeps the eye sharp.
            </div>
            <div class="scene-entry-synopsis">
              <p>Music videos and commercial work, folded together because they live in the same part of the brain — short form, specific brief, make it feel like something. The Tetris piece, <em>Indio</em>, became the Coachella theme.</p>
              <p>The work on this scene keeps the craft muscles loose between longer projects. Every frame is a rehearsal for the next feature.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="scene-entry-actions">
              <a href="#" class="primary">Watch Reel →</a>
              <a href="#">Full Project List</a>
            </div>
          </div>
          <aside class="scene-entry-meta">
            <div class="scene-meta-row"><span class="key">Scene</span><span class="val">04</span></div>
            <div class="scene-meta-row"><span class="key">Status</span><span class="val"><em>Released</em></span></div>
            <div class="scene-meta-row"><span class="key">Format</span><span class="val">Music Video · Commercial</span></div>
            <div class="scene-meta-row"><span class="key">Notable</span><span class="val">Coachella "Indio" Theme</span></div>
          </aside>
        </div>
      </article>

      <!-- SCENE 05 — Development slate -->
      <article class="scene-entry">
        <div class="scene-entry-number">05</div>
        <div class="scene-entry-body">
          <div class="scene-entry-main">
            <div class="scene-slugline">— · Development Slate · Under Wraps</div>
            <h2 class="scene-entry-title">In <em>Development</em></h2>
            <div class="scene-entry-tagline">
              What's next. On the board. Not ready to talk about yet.
            </div>
            <div class="scene-entry-synopsis">
              <span class="prompt">Optional. List one or two projects by working title, or leave this scene block as a gestured hint of slate depth. Delete it entirely if you'd rather not signal development activity publicly.</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <aside class="scene-entry-meta">
            <div class="scene-meta-row"><span class="key">Scene</span><span class="val">05</span></div>
            <div class="scene-meta-row"><span class="key">Status</span><span class="val"><em>In Development</em></span></div>
            <div class="scene-meta-row"><span class="key">Details</span><span class="val">TBA</span></div>
          </aside>
        </div>
      </article>

    </div>
  </section>
</main>

</BaseLayout>
